log_messages: How does the concept of  uniqueness in sets differ  from lists in  Python?

The concept of uniqueness in sets differs from lists in Python. Sets are unordered collections of unique elements. This means that any duplicate elements are automatically removed. Lists, on the other hand, are ordered collections of elements that can include duplicates.
